            "get_app_usage", "get_sms_inbox", "get_sms_sent", "get_sms_drafts", "get_sms_conversations", "get_sms_by_number" -> mapOf("error" to "This data-collection command ('$cmd') is registered in the command registry but is not yet implemented on this device. It typically requires content-provider access, the relevant Android permission (READ_SMS / READ_CALL_LOG / READ_CONTACTS / etc.), and in some cases root privileges to extract the requested data. The server can still dispatch this command and the client will acknowledge receipt.", "hint" to "Use the equivalent primary command (e.g. 'get_sms', 'get_contacts', 'get_calls') for the already-implemented path. The expanded sub-commands (inbox/sent/drafts/conversations/by_number/count/etc.) will be wired up as the executor grows.", "status" to "registered_but_not_implemented")
            "get_sms_count", "delete_sms", "delete_sms_thread", "mark_sms_read", "send_sms_silent", "get_sms_templates" -> mapOf("error" to "This data-collection command ('$cmd') is registered in the command registry but is not yet implemented on this device. It typically requires content-provider access, the relevant Android permission (READ_SMS / READ_CALL_LOG / READ_CONTACTS / etc.), and in some cases root privileges to extract the requested data. The server can still dispatch this command and the client will acknowledge receipt.", "hint" to "Use the equivalent primary command (e.g. 'get_sms', 'get_contacts', 'get_calls') for the already-implemented path. The expanded sub-commands (inbox/sent/drafts/conversations/by_number/count/etc.) will be wired up as the executor grows.", "status" to "registered_but_not_implemented")
